The nature of a brand and related terms. Relationships between brand management and marketing and design. Values and brand architecture. Brand levels: organization, product group, product or service. Specifics, process and necessity of creating personal brands.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide knowledge about the connections between brand management and the discipline of marketing and design management, and to develop the ability to analyze and create brands at both the organizational and individual level.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) know the nature of brand and brand management and the connection with marketing and strategic management of an organization;  2) understand the importance of user focus in the context of brand management;  3) be able to analyze the structure of brands and messages sent to different customer groups; 4) be able to compile initial tasks for writing marketing texts or compile corresponding texts based on the target group;  5) be able to analyze the visual identity of a brand and make related suggestions;  6) know the nature of a personal brand and understand its necessity;  7) be able to develop their personal brand and consciously manage it.
